{
  "text": "[60] As noted in section 1, [CITATION_1] showed that E z_tall and H j _ tall at d = 2 km from a tower of height h = 553 m struck by lightning were 2.6 times larger than E z_flat and H j_flat . They assumed that v = 0.63c, r top = \u00c00.5, and r bot = 0.48 (corresponding, for example, to Z ch = 900 W, Z ob = 300 W, and Z gr = 100 W, in which case r gr = 0.8).",
